00:42:31.529 --> 00:42:34.450
going to be surprised.

00:42:34.450 --> 00:42:40.749
We're going to work on the highest level
and if we succeed we're all going to share

00:42:40.749 --> 00:42:41.749
in the success.

00:42:41.749 --> 00:42:42.749
&gt;&gt;Joel: Cool.

00:42:42.749 --> 00:42:45.650
&gt;&gt;Peter: I'm maybe not answering your question,
I'm talking about

00:42:45.650 --> 00:42:47.599
a way of working.

00:42:47.599 --> 00:42:50.819
There's just so many people I've gotten to
work with

00:42:50.819 --> 00:42:56.210
over the years that if I could just put them
all in a room and we could all just show up

00:42:56.210 --> 00:42:59.809
and I'll come with a story and we'll figure
it out.

00:42:59.809 --> 00:43:04.461
&gt;&gt;Joel: Maybe we'll do that exactly what you're
saying but in space.

00:43:04.461 --> 00:43:05.461
[laughter]

00:43:05.461 --> 00:43:06.461
&gt;&gt;Peter: In space.

00:43:06.461 --> 00:43:11.410
But I will tell you limitations are so useful
and the scenes I'm most proud of in almost

00:43:11.410 --> 00:43:15.989
every film I've made
are ones where we were up against insurmountable

00:43:15.989 --> 00:43:18.099
odds,
particularly in Pieces of April where every

00:43:18.099 --> 00:43:23.339
day
the solutions we found were borne out of time

00:43:23.339 --> 00:43:30.329
and talent and the weather and the light,
